---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import SiteNav from "../components/SiteNav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import PageHeader from "../components/PageHeader.astro";
import Prose from "../components/Prose.astro";

const lastUpdated = "30 April 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — BetsPlug"
  description="How BetsPlug collects, uses and protects your personal data. GDPR-compliant, plain-English."
>
  <SiteNav />

  <main>
    <PageHeader
      kicker="Legal"
      title="Privacy Policy"
      subtitle={`Last updated: ${lastUpdated}`}
    />

    <Prose>
      <h2>1. Who is responsible</h2>
      <p>
        BetsPlug, established in the Netherlands, is the data controller
        for the personal data described below. Reach us at <a
          href="mailto:privacy@betsplug.com">privacy@betsplug.com</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>2. What we collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Account data</strong> — email address, hashed password,
          chosen username, language preference.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Subscription data</strong> — Stripe customer ID,
          subscription tier and billing cycle. Card details stay with
          Stripe; we never see them.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Usage data</strong> — pages viewed, predictions opened,
          IP-derived country, browser and device type. Used for product
          improvement and abuse detection.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Communication data</strong> — emails you send us, support
          tickets, Telegram channel membership status (Platinum tier).
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Why we use it</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To run your account and deliver the predictions you subscribed to.</li>
        <li>To process payments via Stripe and prevent fraud.</li>
        <li>To improve the engine and the user interface based on aggregate usage patterns.</li>
        <li>To answer your support requests.</li>
        <li>To comply with legal obligations (tax, AML, consumer-protection law).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Legal basis (GDPR)</h2>
      <p>
        We process personal data on the basis of (a) the contract you enter
        into when you sign up, (b) your consent for non-essential cookies
        and marketing emails, and (c) our legitimate interest in keeping
        the platform secure and improving it. You can withdraw consent at
        any time without affecting prior processing.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Sharing</h2>
      <p>
        We share data with a small number of processors:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Stripe</strong> — payment processing.</li>
        <li><strong>Vercel + Railway</strong> — hosting infrastructure.</li>
        <li><strong>Sanity</strong> — content management for the blog.</li>
        <li><strong>Resend / Postmark</strong> — transactional email.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We do not sell your data and we do not share it with advertising
        networks.
      </p>

      <h2>6. International transfers</h2>
      <p>
        Some processors operate outside the EU/EEA. Where that's the case
        we rely on Standard Contractual Clauses approved by the European
        Commission to safeguard the transfer.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Retention</h2>
      <p>
        Account data is kept for as long as your account is active and for
        12 months after deletion (legal hold). Anonymous prediction-history
        data is kept indefinitely as part of the public track record.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Your rights</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Access — request a copy of the data we hold about you.</li>
        <li>Rectification — correct inaccurate data.</li>
        <li>Erasure — delete your account and personal data ("right to be forgotten").</li>
        <li>Portability — get your data in a machine-readable format.</li>
        <li>Objection — object to processing based on legitimate interest.</li>
        <li>Complaint — file with your national supervisory authority (in NL: Autoriteit Persoonsgegevens).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>9. Security</h2>
      <p>
        Passwords are stored hashed. Connections are TLS-encrypted. Access
        to production data is restricted to a small team under audit
        logging. We run automated security scans and patch dependencies
        weekly.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        See our <a href="/cookies">cookie page</a> for the full breakdown.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Privacy questions or data-rights requests: <a
          href="mailto:privacy@betsplug.com">privacy@betsplug.com</a>. We
        respond within 30 days.
      </p>
    </Prose>

    <Footer />
  </main>
</Layout>
